## How Students Navigate This Structure

### Entry Point: README.md

Students start here and follow this flow:

```
README.md
    â†“
    â”œâ”€â†’ In-Class Activities
    â”‚   â””â”€â†’ guides/github-setup-guide.md
    â”‚   â””â”€â†’ templates/team-contract-template.md
    â”‚   â””â”€â†’ guides/problem-statement-guide.md
    â”‚
    â””â”€â†’ Homework
        â”œâ”€â†’ homework-assignment.md (detailed requirements)
        â”œâ”€â†’ templates/capstone-proposal-template.md
        â”œâ”€â†’ templates/repo-structure.md
        â””â”€â†’ guides/irb-light-guide.md (if needed)
```

### Linear vs. Reference Content

**Linear (read in order):**
1. README.md
2. homework-assignment.md
3. Relevant guides (as needed)

**Reference (look up as needed):**
- Templates (copy when ready to work)
- Troubleshooting sections in guides
- Examples (for inspiration)

